<p><u></u>We know that as the field adapts to our changing society, the MCH Leadership Competencies will need further updating to support the growth of our leaders.  We encourage ongoing input from each of you as we continue to refine the Competencies.<u></u><u></u></p>
<p><img src="../images/new-competencies.jpg" width="1000" height="552" alt="New Competencies" /></p>
<p><u></u>So, what&rsquo;s next? Now that the document has been finalized, we will work  to update the self-assessment and the corresponding resources and trainings.  We are currently working on a four-step process to update the MCH Navigator to reflect the new competencies. We hope to have completed our updates by fall 2018. </p>
<p>Our 4-pronged approach involves: </p>
<ol>
  <li>Re-programming the database that serves as the underlying structure for our learning opportunities</li>
  <li>Converting our webpages that run independently from the database</li>
  <li>Updating our microlearning programs to reflect the new competencies</li>
  <li>Converting our online Self-Assessment: <em>After analysis of the overall themes reported on by the  self-assessment, we have determined that you can continue using this  version of the tool until the new tool has been released. Data from both  tools will be comparable.</em></li>
</ol>
<p>During this time, you will be able to use all features of the MCH Navigator.</p>
